other_tests.findings: Extensive heterotopic ossification involving soft tissues and muscles surrounding the bilateral humeri and proximal ulnae, bilateral femurs, and bilateral tibias/fibulas.

other_tests.procedure_name: Computed tomography of the chest, abdomen, and pelvis
other_tests.findings: Extensive ossifications of the muscles including the right latissimus dorsi, left scalene, bilateral pectoralis, bilateral external oblique abdominal, right iliacus, bilateral gluteal, left adductor, and left hamstring; involvement of the subcutaneous tissues without evidence of pulmonary fibrosis.
A novel de novo heterozygous, likely pathogenic variant in the FAM111B (c.1462delT, p.Cys488Valfs*21) was identified.
